---
import DocLayout from "../../layouts/DocLayout.astro";
---

<DocLayout
    title="Getting Started — Gsheetbase"
    description="Turn your Google Sheet into a REST API in under five minutes."
>
    <div class="max-w-none">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-3 text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100">
            Getting Started
        </h1>
        <p
            class="text-lg text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 mb-10 leading-relaxed"
        >
            Gsheetbase converts any Google Sheet into a live REST API. This
            guide walks you from zero to your first API call in about five
            minutes.
        </p>

        <!-- Step 1 -->
        <div class="mb-10">
            <h2
                class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"
            >
                <span
                    class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center"
                    >1</span
                >
                Sign in with Google
            </h2>
            <p
                class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-0"
            >
                Go to <a
                    href="https://app.gsheetbase.com"
                    class="text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80"
                    >app.gsheetbase.com</a
                >
                and click <strong
                    class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200"
                    >Sign in with Google</strong
                >. Gsheetbase uses OAuth 2.0 and only requests <code
                    class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
                    >spreadsheets.readonly</code
                > scope by default. You can grant write access later from the dashboard
                when you need it.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 2 -->
        <div class="mb-10">
            <h2
                class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"
            >
                <span
                    class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center"
                    >2</span
                >
                Find your Spreadsheet ID
            </h2>
            <p
                class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3"
            >
                Open any Google Sheet. The Spreadsheet ID is the long string in
                the URL between <code
                    class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
                    >/d/</code
                > and <code
                    class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
                    >/edit</code
                >:
            </p>
            <pre
                class="bg-slate-900 text-green-400 text-xs rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code>{`https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1BxiMVs0XRA5nFMdKvBdBZjgmUUqptlbs74OgVE2upms/edit
                                       └─────────── Spreadsheet ID ───────────────┘`}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 3 -->
        <div class="mb-10">
            <h2
                class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"
            >
                <span
                    class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center"
                    >3</span
                >
                Register the sheet
            </h2>
            <p
                class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3"
            >
                In the Gsheetbase dashboard click <strong
                    class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200"
                    >Add Sheet</strong
                >, paste your Spreadsheet ID, give it a name, and save. This
                registers the sheet in your account without copying any data.
            </p>
            <p
                class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3"
            >
                You can also register programmatically once you have a session
                JWT:
            </p>
            <pre
                class="bg-slate-900 text-green-400 text-xs rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code>{`curl -X POST https://api.gsheetbase.com/api/sheets/register \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{ "sheet_id": "1BxiMVs0XRA5nFM...", "sheet_name": "Products" }'`}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 4 -->
        <div class="mb-10">
            <h2
                class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"
            >
                <span
                    class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center"
                    >4</span
                >
                Publish &amp; get your API key
            </h2>
            <p
                class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3"
            >
                Select the registered sheet in the dashboard and click
                <strong class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200"
                    >Publish</strong
                >. Gsheetbase generates a unique API key and immediately exposes
                the sheet as a REST endpoint. Copy the key — you will use it in
                every request.
            </p>
            <p
                class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 text-xs mb-2 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide"
            >
                Via the management API
            </p>
            <pre
                class="bg-slate-900 text-green-400 text-xs rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code>{`curl -X POST https://api.gsheetbase.com/api/sheets/{id}/publish \\
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT" \\
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \\
  -d '{ "default_range": "Sheet1", "use_first_row_as_header": true }'

# Response
{
  "message": "sheet published successfully",
  "api_key": "gsb_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
}`}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 5 -->
        <div class="mb-10">
            <h2
                class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"
            >
                <span
                    class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-primary/10 text-primary text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center"
                    >5</span
                >
                Fetch your data
            </h2>
            <p
                class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-3"
            >
                Use the API key in the URL path on the worker endpoint. By
                default the first row of your sheet is treated as column
                headers.
            </p>
            <pre
                class="bg-slate-900 text-green-400 text-xs rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed mb-4"><code>{`curl "https://worker.gsheetbase.com/v1/gsb_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx"
# Returns all rows from the default sheet tab

curl "https://worker.gsheetbase.com/v1/gsb_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx?collection=Sheet2&limit=10"
# Returns first 10 rows from the Sheet2 tab`}</code></pre>
            <p
                class="text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-500 text-xs mb-2 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide"
            >
                Example JSON response
            </p>
            <pre
                class="bg-slate-900 text-green-400 text-xs rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto leading-relaxed"><code>{`{
  "data": [
    { "name": "Apple", "price": "1.20", "in_stock": "true" },
    { "name": "Banana", "price": "0.80", "in_stock": "true" }
  ]
}`}</code></pre>
        </div>

        <!-- Step 6 -->
        <div class="mb-10">
            <h2
                class="text-xl font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2"
            >
                <span
                    class="flex-shrink-0 w-7 h-7 rounded-full bg-slate-200 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-500 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm font-bold flex items-center justify-center"
                    >6</span
                >
                Enable write access <span
                    class="text-sm font-normal text-slate-400">(optional)</span
                >
            </h2>
            <p
                class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400 text-sm leading-relaxed"
            >
                By default the API is read-only. To allow
                <code
                    class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
                    >POST</code
                >,
                <code
                    class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
                    >PUT</code
                >,
                <code
                    class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
                    >PATCH</code
                >, or
                <code
                    class="text-xs bg-slate-100 dark:bg-slate-700 text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded"
                    >DELETE</code
                >, open the sheet's <strong
                    class="font-semibold text-slate-800 dark:text-slate-200"
                    >Write Settings</strong
                > in the dashboard and toggle the methods you need. Gsheetbase will
                prompt you to grant write scope to your Google account if you haven't
                already.
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Next steps -->
        <div class="border-t border-slate-200 dark:border-slate-700 pt-8 mt-8">
            <h2
                class="text-lg font-semibold text-slate-900 dark:text-slate-100 mb-4"
            >
                Next steps
            </h2>
            <ul class="space-y-2">
                <li
                    class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
                >
                    <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5 text-primary flex-shrink-0"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        ><path
                            stroke-linecap="round"
                            stroke-linejoin="round"
                            d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path></svg
                    >
                    <span
                        >Read the <a
                            href="/docs/api-reference"
                            class="text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80"
                            >API Reference</a
                        > for all query parameters and HTTP methods.</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li
                    class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
                >
                    <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5 text-primary flex-shrink-0"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        ><path
                            stroke-linecap="round"
                            stroke-linejoin="round"
                            d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path></svg
                    >
                    <span
                        >Browse <a
                            href="/docs/examples"
                            class="text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80"
                            >Examples</a
                        > for copy-paste curl and JavaScript snippets.</span
                    >
                </li>
                <li
                    class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
                >
                    <svg
                        xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
                        class="w-4 h-4 mt-0.5 text-primary flex-shrink-0"
                        fill="none"
                        viewBox="0 0 24 24"
                        stroke="currentColor"
                        stroke-width="2"
                        ><path
                            stroke-linecap="round"
                            stroke-linejoin="round"
                            d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"></path></svg
                    >
                    <span
                        >Check the <a
                            href="/docs/faq"
                            class="text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-80"
                            >FAQ</a
                        > for questions about authentication, rate limits, and security.</span
                    >
                </li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
</DocLayout>
